  <data key="d3">18.0</data>
  <data key="d4">"Delay neurons are a specific type of neuron within the prefrontal cortex that are active during cognitive processes like memory and anticipation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Delay neurons are located and active in the prefrontal cortex, where they play a key role in encoding reward position and anticipating action vectors."</data>
  <data key="d5">"brain structure, neural activity"&lt;SEP&gt;"component, neural mechanism"</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e9f17dfb333219cce1353f879de8deae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f736994c87df07b89d48f895b0862dfe</data>
