  <data key="d3">10.0</data>
  <data key="d4">"The cold part is a subdivision of the prefrontal cortex, located at the top, responsible for cold functions like planning and reasoning."</data>
  <data key="d5">"part-of, subdivision"</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-831d96d12ba52ebdde5127ea0b27984d</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CORTEX PRÉFRONTAL&quot;" target="&quot;LIBRE ARBITRE&quot;">
  <data key="d3">8.0</data>
  <data key="d4">"The prefrontal cortex provides a margin of freedom between perception and action, which is presented as the neural basis for discussions on free will and voluntary action."</data>
  <data key="d5">"free will, neural basis"</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-f736994c87df07b89d48f895b0862dfe</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CORTEX PRÉFRONTAL&quot;" target="&quot;ABSTRACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d3">9.0</data>
  <data key="d4">"The prefrontal cortex is essential for abstract thought, enabling the imagination of things that do not exist concretely."</data>
  <data key="d5">"abstract thinking, imagination"</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-b6c33ae2e365cd0a1d3d8102409d7912</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CORTEX PRÉFRONTAL&quot;" target="&quot;PARTIE CHAUDE&quot;">
  <data key="d3">10.0</data>
  <data key="d4">"The hot part is a subdivision of the prefrontal cortex, located near the orbits, responsible for hot functions like motivation and emotion regulation."</data>
  <data key="d5">"part-of, subdivision"</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-831d96d12ba52ebdde5127ea0b27984d</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CORTEX PRÉFRONTAL&quot;" target="&quot;APATHIE&quot;">
  <data key="d3">8.0</data>
  <data key="d4">"Dysfunction of the prefrontal cortex leads to apathy, as explained by Richard Lévy."</data>
  <data key="d5">"cause-effect, neurological"</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-cef3ed8b278fc8ecffbe23ed1293fa7a</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CORTEX PRÉFRONTAL&quot;" target="&quot;RAISON&quot;">
  <data key="d3">9.0</data>
  <data key="d4">"The prefrontal cortex houses the rational, planning, and cold cognitive functions referred to as reason."</data>
  <data key="d5">"cognitive function, rationality"</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-5a0e0f31ff75981ae7f4e27b231396b7</data>
</edge>
<edge source="&quot;CORTEX PRÉFRONTAL&quot;" target="&quot;ÂME&quot;">
  <data key="d3">9.0</data>
