<edge source="&quot;RICHARD LÉVY&quot;" target="&quot;CORTEX PRÉFRONTAL&quot;">
  <data key="d3">94.0</data>
  <data key="d4">"Richard Lévy attributes the ability to contextualize and relativize values to the prefrontal cortex."&lt;SEP&gt;"Richard Lévy discusses the prefrontal cortex, explaining its division and functions in detail."&lt;SEP&gt;"Richard Lévy discusses the prefrontal cortex, its late maturation, and its role as the conductor of cognitive style."&lt;SEP&gt;"Richard Lévy discusses the role of the prefrontal cortex in handshakes and its relevance in dementia."&lt;SEP&gt;"Richard Lévy explains the dual nature of the prefrontal cortex, dividing it into cold (reason) and hot (soul) parts, and emphasizes its late maturation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Richard Lévy explains the role of the prefrontal cortex as the conductor of the brain, organizing thoughts and behaviors."&lt;SEP&gt;"Richard Lévy identifies the prefrontal cortex as the brain region responsible for creating abstract values and for the contextualization/relativization that allows values like turnips to change."&lt;SEP&gt;"Richard Lévy uses the function and integrity of the prefrontal cortex as key evidence to support his argument for degrees of freedom and internal deliberation."&lt;SEP&gt;"Richard Lévy's research and explanations focus on the prefrontal cortex, describing its role in working memory, action preparation, and providing a margin of freedom for voluntary actions."</data>
  <data key="d5">"brain function, value creation"&lt;SEP&gt;"brain region, function"&lt;SEP&gt;"expertise, brain structure"&lt;SEP&gt;"expertise, explanation"&lt;SEP&gt;"explanation, brain region"&lt;SEP&gt;"neurological explanation, brain function"&lt;SEP&gt;"neuroscientific evidence, argument support"&lt;SEP&gt;"research focus, brain function"</data>
  <data key="d6">chunk-e9f17dfb333219cce1353f879de8deae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef9367e0b21550ebdb56758dc0bde39a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-831d96d12ba52ebdde5127ea0b27984d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-696e6532b6fd5570de4d3650523b608e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f736994c87df07b89d48f895b0862dfe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1161f1eb6f483238105e2fc6b85fde00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a0e0f31ff75981ae7f4e27b231396b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cef3ed8b278fc8ecffbe23ed1293fa7a</data>
</edge>
